description.narrative:
The current project aims to improve the living conditions of around 2,000 small-scale farmers in the province of Nampula, by enabling them to access fair markets of sesame, cashew nuts and peanuts. These commodities were chosen because of the potential to producethese crops in the selected districts (favorable agro ecological conditions and existing knowledge and skills from local farmers) and the good national and international potential of these crops (in normal seasons 50% can be sold internationally). With a total budget of 392,250 Euros, this project will be jointly implemented between Oxfam and AENA (a local NGO based in the Nampula province). AENA will do direct implementation of the activities with the beneficiaries and other stakeholders, Oxfamwill have the monitoring role and will provide its# expertise in value chain development programs.

GOAL: To improve the livelihood (mainly food security and family income) of small scale farmers through creating an enabling environment for Fair Trade of sesame, cashew nuts and peanuts in 4districts of the Nampula province in Mozambique.
STRATEGIC OBJECTIVE: To develop a robust platform composed of 2,000 individual andaggregated farmers in 4 districts of the Nampula province (Meconta, Monapo, Muecateand Murrupula).
Outcomes
1. Viable agribusiness cooperatives/associations effectively linked to a more fair value chain;
2. 2000 farmers increases their average productivity (kg per hectare) by at least 80%;
3. 2000 farmers increased their average profit income by US$ 200 per year;
